      <p outputclass="ps_para_number" id="UUID-cd3834e3-9ff9-6054-6464-0912a1d75d48_aag-afi9.15" class="- topic/p ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">9.15</b>Â Under FASB ASC 815, the convertible bonds
                    are hybrid instruments that should be separated into two components: straight
                    interest-bearing bonds and a conversion option. Each component should be
                    accounted for separately, with the bonds (the host contract) accounted for as
                    available-for-sale securities under FASB ASC 320 and the option accounted for as
                    an embedded derivative under FASB ASC 815. Martin estimates the fair value of
                    the straight bonds by subtracting the fair value of the embedded option from the
                    basis of the hybrid instrument.</p>
